{"type":"message","id":"b58ebe6b","parentId":"bdd76adb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:55:49.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"d40b955382637849e2941533c26915d89f981b4c20bbf1dbf0828e4e565360b3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jsdargdzgi1j_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 075514.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":633,"output":62,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12832,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353347397}}
{"type":"message","id":"03cd8f02","parentId":"b58ebe6b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:55:49.372Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jsdargdzgi1j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 075514\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The user is working on Breakaway - a stateless discontinuous agent\r\n2. They've completed several phases and are now focused on the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n3. The next action should be implementing the TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n4. I need to provide one concrete action that advances the goals\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step would be to:\r\n1. First examine the existing pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Then implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse log files exist and their format, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the recent note: \"Just applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\" - this suggests there may already be some experiment documentation.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Check the structure of existing pulse logs\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me provide a focused action that advances the TIC experiment forward.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires analyzing `logs/pulse_*.md` files for invariant/variant patterns, but I need to first verify the actual structure and content of these logs to build an effective classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation that reads pulse logs, extracts temporal features, classifies invariants vs variants, and measures accuracy against the >70% success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Implementation: 2026-03-24 0755\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\nClassifies pulse log content as invariant (stable across sessions) vs variant (changing).\r\nHypothesis: Invariants = causal structure; compression finds causation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass PulseFeatures:\r\n    path: Path\r\n    timestamp: str\r\n    goals_section: str\r\n    pending_section: str\r\n    notes_section: str\r\n    action_section: str\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_path: Path) -> PulseFeatures:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections using markdown headers\r\n    goals = re.search(r'## Goals:(.*?)(?=##|$)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    pending = re.search(r'## Pending:(.*?)(?=##|$)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    notes = re.search(r'## Notes(.*?)(?=##|$)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action = re.search(r'### ACTION\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|$)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract timestamp from filename or content\r\n    ts_match = re.search(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}', pulse_path.name)\r\n    timestamp = ts_match.group(0) if ts_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    return PulseFeatures(\r\n        path=pulse_path,\r\n        timestamp=timestamp,\r\n        goals_section=goals.group(1).strip() if goals else \"\",\r\n        pending_section=pending.group(1).strip() if pending else \"\",\r\n        notes_section=notes.group(1).strip() if notes else \"\",\r\n        action_section=action.group(1).strip() if action else \"\"\r\n    )\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(features_list: list[PulseFeatures]) -> dict[str, int]:\r\n    \"\"\"Find content that appears across multiple pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n    all_lines = []\r\n    for f in features_list:\r\n        # Split into lines and normalize\r\n        lines = f.goals_section.split('\\n') + f.pending_section.split('\\n')\r\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in lines if l.strip() and not l.startswith('- [ ]')]\r\n        all_lines.extend(lines)\r\n    \r\n    # Count occurrences\r\n    return Counter(all_lines)\r\n\r\ndef classify_temporal_patterns(pulse1: PulseFeatures, pulse2: PulseFeatures) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify what's invariant vs variant between two consecutive pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    f1_invariants = set(pulse1.goals_section.split('\\n')) | set(pulse1.pending_section.split('\\n'))\r\n    f2_invariants = set(pulse2.goals_section.split('\\n')) | set(pulse2.pending_section.split('\\n'))\r\n    \r\n    stable = f1_invariants & f2_invariants\r\n    changed = f1_invariants ^ f2_invariants\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant_count': len(stable),\r\n        'variant_count': len(changed),\r\n        'stability_ratio': len(stable) / (len(f1_invariants) + len(f2_invariants)) if (len(f1_invariants) + len(f2_invariants)) > 0 else 0\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(previous: PulseFeatures, invariants: dict[str, int]) -> set[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what will be invariant in next pulse based on past patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    prev_lines = set(previous.goals_section.split('\\n') + previous.pending_section.split('\\n'))\r\n    \r\n    # Lines that have appeared 2+ times are likely invariants\r\n    predicted_invariants = {line for line, count in invariants.items() if count >= 2}\r\n    \r\n    return predicted_invariants & prev_lines\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment(log_dir: str = \"logs\", min_pulses: int = 5):\r\n    \"\"\"Run the full TIC\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 07:55:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353349370}}
